INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("264", "1", "2012-08-29 11:24:31", "2012-08-29 11:24:31", "<strong>Anyone want to buy a kidney?</strong>\r\n\r\nWhen you’re a cyclist, boarder, surfer, skater or do any other sport which involves a piece of equipment, you’re bombarded by “The Next Best Thing” which promises to make you stronger, faster, better, higher, gnarlier or more attractive to the opposite sex. I\'ve always thought that\'s a load of cock and balls.\r\n\r\nUntil now, because I have fallen in love.\r\n<h2>Making the Transition</h2>\r\nI’d never really paid much attention to Transition bikes before, as they always seem a bit too exotic and niche to be a realistic bike for me. Guys in videos who can ride a shit load better than me will flash the frame decal whilst doing some amazing super slow-mo tabletop, winking at the camera, as if to say “I deserve this bike because I can do this on it. Can you?”\r\n\r\nThis beauty, which made parts of me sit up and pay attention, is the Transition Bikes  Covert Carbon Fibre – although I think the Covert part is ironic with this paint job.\r\n<h2>COCK &amp; BALLS of Iron(y)</h2>\r\nIf fact, there’s a lot of irony around this bike – the fact that the technology they’ve created to build the thing is “COCK and BALLS” technology (explained in this very informative film: <a href=\"https://vimeo.com/45041994\">https://vimeo.com/45041994</a>) goes some way to explaining that Transition have a sense of humour.\r\n\r\nPerhaps the most ironic thing is the simple fact that I must have it but there\'s no way I can afford it. The frame and shock only price is a monsterous £2,399 – with a full bike build starting at £4,750!?! It would seem that Transition really do have a sense of humour and are laughing at me and my puny bank balance.\r\n\r\nI have a plan to eventually own this bike but it involves selling an internal organ or two, which - ironically – means I’ll have to recover before I’ll be able to ride it.", "Transition Covert", "", "publish", "closed", "open", "", "transition-covert", "", "", "2012-08-29 13:21:08", "2012-08-29 13:21:08", "", "0", "http://escpd.com/?p=264", "0", "post", "", "0");
