INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("1090", "1", "2012-10-09 09:48:47", "2012-10-09 09:48:47", "I am the God of Hell Fire and I bring you... HELLRAZOR!!!\r\n\r\nGet ready to raise some hell and cause havoc with this super versatile board.  The Hellrazor takes all the heritage of it\'s ancestors the Spitfire and Hellfire, adds some modern refinery, creating a kick-ass performance hybrid.\r\n\r\nThe overall volume of the board is smaller with a thinned down nose and tail, offering more maneuverability and agility add a twist of squared edge, bake for 30mins and get yourself a sweet board for vertical snaps.\r\n\r\nCheck out the full range of Firewire boards <a title=\"firewire surfboards\" href=\"http://www.firewiresurfboards.com/\">here</a>.", "Firewire Hellrazor", "", "inherit", "closed", "open", "", "1085-revision-4", "", "", "2012-10-09 09:48:47", "2012-10-09 09:48:47", "", "1085", "http://escpd.com/1085-revision-4/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("1088", "1", "2012-10-09 09:18:25", "2012-10-09 09:18:25", "versatile board that is designed to work in just about any type of surf in the waist to head high range.  Notice how the tail has been thinned out, and it has a great squared off edge for vertical snaps.\r\n\r\nThe grandchild of the <a href=\"http://www.firewiresurfboards.com/quiver_boards.php?boardid=spitfire\" target=\"_blank\">Spitfire</a>, this new shortboard has a solid performance hybrid heritage. The <a href=\"http://www.firewiresurfboards.com/quiver_boards.php?boardid=hellrazor\" target=\"_blank\">Hell Razor</a> retains many of the features that made the <a href=\"http://www.firewiresurfboards.com/quiver_boards.php?boardid=spitfire\" target=\"_blank\">Spitfire</a> and <a href=\"http://www.firewiresurfboards.com/quiver_boards.php?boardid=hellfire\" target=\"_blank\">Hellfire</a> successful, and refines a few to crank out some extra mojo. The super deep concaves have been flattened out a bit, and the nose and tail have been shaved down to a narrower look. This board still keeps the width though, so you won’t bog out on flat sections. Overall it will give you a bit more maneuverability at the cost of overall volume, and is a solid refinement of the Hellfire series. The <a href=\"http://www.firewiresurfboards.com/quiver_boards.php?boardid=hellrazor\" target=\"_blank\">Hell Razor</a> fits well into the 3′ to 6′ wave category, and is a great compliment to a hybrid like the <a href=\"http://www.firewiresurfboards.com/quiver_boards.php?boardid=dominator\" target=\"_blank\">Dominator</a>/<a href=\"http://www.firewiresurfboards.com/quiver_boards.php?boardid=spitfire\" target=\"_blank\">Spitfire</a>. Use your hybrid on windy or smaller days, but when it cleans up or gets a bit larger pull out the <a href=\"http://www.firewiresurfboards.com/quiver_boards.php?boardid=hellrazor\" target=\"_blank\">Hell Razor</a> to cause some havoc. Ride this one 1″ shorter than your performance shortboard", "Firewire Hellrazor", "", "inherit", "closed", "open", "", "1085-revision-2", "", "", "2012-10-09 09:18:25", "2012-10-09 09:18:25", "", "1085", "http://escpd.com/1085-revision-2/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
