INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("1410", "1", "2012-11-11 16:20:34", "2012-11-11 16:20:34", "\"So I Loooooooovvvvvvveeeeee snowboarding and I am also a massive geek as my friends running this site often like to remind me.  So something I have wondered about (whilst waiting for mates to catch me up on the hill) is how could I merge these two awesome passions together.  Why would you ever want to do that I hear you ask!? Surly snowboarding is all about the escapism of modern life and this is definitely  true even in my nerdy case.  However havn\'t you ever wondered when your shredding it down an early morning black whether you really are close to breaking the speed of sound? Well wonder no longer my pow hunting friends Oakley have gone and created a set of goggles that are truly SMART!\n\nOakley Airwave™ combine the company\'s best goggle technologies with a heads-up display that integrates GPS, Bluetooth, and more with a host of onboard sensors to bring new possibilities to your alpine experience.  Picture the scene your just about to drop into some sick back country lines and you want to get the most out of this amazing experience! you wanna know how much your killing it!  Wouldn\'t it be awesome if you had someone with you able to tell you how fast, how high, how narly things really are? Thats what Oakley Airwave\'s can do! not to mention making you feel like a fighter pilot with their amazing heads-up display beaming info direct to your eye ball whilst riding.  Information such as current altitude, speed, location, directions, airtime, and distance travelled.  They even let you boast with confidence after stomping massive air by tracking distance, height and airtime of jump and if you need some inspiration to achieve some decent stats they even let you listen to, control, and see whats on your ipod/iphone through their built in headphones and bluetooth connectivity.\n\nWhen you nearing the end of an awesome day of back country heli boarding these goggles still have more to give, when you pilot is ready to pick you up (I know this happens all the time!) they will display his text direct to the goggles and because they are linked to your smart phone they even display tracking details to find him and your other skier? mates incase they had a yard sale on the way down and couldn\'t keep up!  As if all of that wasn\'t enough their is an open SDK for these goggles, what the hell?? well lets just put it like this Apples app store is built on an open SDK and look what you can find in there!! \"", "Oakley Airwave", "", "inherit", "closed", "open", "", "1407-revision-2", "", "", "2012-11-11 16:20:34", "2012-11-11 16:20:34", "", "1407", "http://escpd.com/1407-revision-2/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
