INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("1874", "1", "2013-01-08 13:06:27", "2013-01-08 13:06:27", "The Pedigree continues...\n\nArguably Ozone\'s flagship foil kite, the Frenzy has been leading the way in traction kiting since I can remember and now it\'s finding it\'s home more and more within the snow-kiting world.\n\nSo what\'s new to 2013?\n\nThe leading edge is partly closed with a mesh covering the intakes to ensure clean air flow while stopping and snow or dirt from entering the wing. Ozone have introduced a new rib technology using diagonal ribs which has allowed them to reduce the bridal points and therefore less lines and a performance increase of 28%!  Another \"new to 2013\" is the \'Link-Line\' this line connects \"both sides of the speed system together to maintain the correct distance between both sides of the kite\".  This not only increases the wing\'s stability but maintains the kites shape when using the landing system. There are also more cells for a cleaner airflow, new, better designed pulleys, \"blow-out valves when you dump the kite into the ground and much more.\n\nAll these improvements make this great kite even greaterer! It has enhanced stability, improved and faster handling resulting in better light wind performance, and giving you the grunt you want in those perfect conditions to rip up any line you want to take.\n\nTime to increase and update my quiver for this snow season!\n\n<a href=\"http://escpd.com/?attachment_id=1871\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1871\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1871\" alt=\"ozone-frenzy2013-colours\" src=\"http://escpd.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ozone-frenzy2013-colours.jpg\" width=\"966\" height=\"594\" /></a>", "Ozone Frenzy 2013", "", "inherit", "closed", "open", "", "1869-revision-2", "", "", "2013-01-08 13:06:27", "2013-01-08 13:06:27", "", "1869", "http://escpd.com/1869-revision-2/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
