INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("1943", "1", "2013-01-10 20:13:22", "2013-01-10 20:13:22", "This skate-style lid by Giro has all the elements needed to make it a great helmet. With an integrated polycarbonate hard outer shell and inner EPS liner it weights in at a mere 315g! Giros Fit Kit™ Pad System allows you to adjust the thickness of the comfort pads on the interior of the helmet, this makes the helmet feel like it\'s a part of your body and not a loose component like many other helmets.\n\nThe guys at Giro have also designed the helmet with something they call Super Fit™. This gives the rider a massive field of vision and means the helmet works perfectly with those expensive <a title=\"Sunglasses\" href=\"http://escpd.com/wildherats-late-nights-tortuga/\">sunglasses</a> and <a title=\"Snowboarding Goggles\" href=\"http://escpd.com/favourite-8-2013-snow-goggles/\">Goggles</a> you just bought!\n\nThe Giro Section is available in an abundance of awesome colours and designs", "Giro Section™", "", "inherit", "closed", "open", "", "1936-revision-6", "", "", "2013-01-10 20:13:22", "2013-01-10 20:13:22", "", "1936", "http://escpd.com/1936-revision-6/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("1941", "1", "2013-01-10 20:03:45", "2013-01-10 20:03:45", "This skate-style lid by Giro has all the elements needed to make it a great helmet. With an integrated polycarbonate hard outer shell and inner EPS liner it weights in at a mere 315g! Giros trademark Fit Kit™ Pad System allows you adjust the thickness of the comfort pads on the interior of the helmet, this makes the helmet feel like it\'s a part of your body and not a loose component like many of the helmets available...not naming any names...\n\nThe guys at Giro have also designed the helmet with something they call Super Fit™. This allows plenty of room for sunglasses, goggles and stops the helmet from obstructing the riders field of vision. Infact, Super Fit™ increases\n\nFIT KIT™ PAD SYSTEM\n\nOur Fit Kit pads system allows you to dial in your fit using different thickness comfort pads on the interior of the helmet. Just pull the hook and loop backed pads out and swap them out for the thickness you need.\n\nThe Section takes the skate-style look to a higher level. Its low-profile shape is distinct yet minimal, and because the shell and EPS liner are integrated though our in-mold construction process, we’re able to save lots of weight. We’ve also optimized the front of the helmet to work great with our sunglasses and goggles, something we call Super Fit™. And with a wide range of graphics, there’s a Section to suit any taste or preference.", "Giro Section™", "", "inherit", "closed", "open", "", "1936-revision-4", "", "", "2013-01-10 20:03:45", "2013-01-10 20:03:45", "", "1936", "http://escpd.com/1936-revision-4/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
