INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("2081", "1", "2013-01-30 13:22:16", "2013-01-30 13:22:16", "All Mountain is the new Freeride.\n\nWe\'ve got eight of our favourite \"do it all\" bikes for 2012 and 2013.\n<h2>Giant Reign X</h2>\nThis is a big bike built for the big times but with Giant\'s Maestro suspension system, climbing isn\'t too much of a problem when you\'re honking up to the next steep bit.\n\nPrice (frame only): £1,399\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Giant Reign X\" href=\"http://www.giant-bicycles.com/en-gb/bikes/model/2013.giant.reign.x.frameset/11855/56876/#technologies\">Learn more about the Giant Reign X here</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[image here]http://www.giant-bicycles.com/en-gb/bikes/model/2013.giant.reign.x.frameset/11855/56876/#technologies\n<h2>Independent Fabrications Ti Deluxe</h2>\nNo favourite list would be complete without a Titanium bike, would it? IF only make a couple of mountain bike frames, but those they do make are pretty amazing and should last a lifetime. This is the only hardtail on this list and does have relatively short travel for our All Mountain category, but the forgiving qualities of Ti mean this would be a capable machine for those wishing to go large.\n\nPrice (frame only): $3,595\n\n[image]http://www.ifbikes.com/assets/images/products//TiD_w1.jpg\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Independent Fabrications Ti Deluxe\" href=\"http://www.ifbikes.com/OurBikes/Off_Road/Ti_Deluxe/\">Learn more about the Independent Fabrications Ti Deluxe</a>\n<h2>Lapierre Spicy 916</h2>\nIt\'s Carbon, it\'s built for multi-World Champion downhill rider Nico Vouilloz\'s attempts to win the Enduro series and Mégavalanches.\nIt\'s light, it\'s tough, it looks great.\n\nPrices from £4,000\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Lapierre Spicy 916\" href=\"http://www.lapierre-bikes.co.uk/mtb/big-mountain-dirt/spicy/spicy-916\">Learn more about the Lapierre Spicy 916</a>\n\n[image]http://www.lapierre-bikes.co.uk/mtb/big-mountain-dirt/spicy/spicy-916\n<h2>Yeti 575</h2>\nYeti have been around for many, many years. It was a Yeti C-26 which John Tomac put some drop bars on for the 1990 World Champs in Durango.\nWell, they\'ve come a long, long way since then and the 575 shows they\'ve learnt a thing or two about putting gorgeous looking bikes together.\nShort, light and flickable but burly and robust - great for whatever you chuck yourself at.\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Yeti 575\" href=\"http://www.yeticycles.com/#/bikes/575\">Learn more about the Yeti 575</a>\n\n[image] http://www.yeticycles.com/#/bikes/575\n<h2>Santa Cruz Nomad Carbon</h2>\nI\'ve posted this bike in full <a title=\"Santa Cruz Carbon Nomad\" href=\"http://escpd.com/santa-cruz-carbon-nomad/\">on here previously</a>, so I won\'t risk repeating myself.\nIt\'s an awesome bike and one which would sit in my shed asking me when we\'re next going out.\nAwesome in white, most awesome in matte black.\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Santa Cruz Nomad Carbon \" href=\"http://www.santacruzbicycles.com/nomad_carbon/\">Learn more about the Santa Cruz Nomad Carbon\n\n</a>\n\nPrices from £4,000\n\n[image]http://brimages.bikeboardmedia.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/santa-cruz-carbon-fiber-nomad2.jpg\n<h2>Devinci Dixon Carbon RX Evo</h2>\nNo country has better facilities for gnarly mountain biking than Canada - and that\'s where Devinci rip up the trails with their uber-steeds.\nHere\'s what they say about the Dixon: \"This hammer strong bike is pure stoke.\"\nI\'ve ridden one and I\'m like totally dialled into that, braa.\nLeonardo would say the same.\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Devinci Dixon Carbon RX Evo\" href=\"http://www.devinci.com/bikes/bike_326_scategory_83\">Learn more about the Devinci Dixon Carbon RX Evo\n\n</a>\n\nPrice: £3,599\n\n<a title=\"Freeborn Bikes\" href=\"http://www.freeborn.co.uk/devinci-dixon-carbon-rx-bike-2013\">Buy online from Freeborn Bicycles\n\n</a>\n\n[image]http://assets1.freeborn.co.uk/media/catalog/product/cache/1/image/5e06319eda06f020e43594a9c230972d/2/0/2013---dixon_carbon_rx.jpg\n<h2>Commencal Meta AM 1</h2>\nIt\'s a pretty sure bet that if you live and work in the Alps and design bikes which rule in the high mountains.\nAndorra based Commencal do just that and the Meta AM1 is one of the best trail sleds you can get.\n\nPrice: £3,999.99\n\n<a title=\"Buy online from ChainReactioncycles\" href=\"http://www.chainreactioncycles.com/Models.aspx?ModelID=83508&amp;gclid=CKXHm7eTkLUCFebLtAodxTgApg\">Buy online from ChainReactioncycles\n\n</a><a title=\"Learn more about the Commencal Meta AM1\" href=\"http://www.commencal-store.co.uk/PBSCProduct.asp?ItmID=10252609\">Learn more about the Commencal Meta AM1\n\n&lt;iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/53141820\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;\n\n</a>\n\n[image]http://www.commencal.com/web_bicycles/2013/HD_2013/bikes_2013/all_mountain/META_AM1_013.jpg", "Favor8 All Mountain Bikes", "", "inherit", "closed", "open", "", "2065-revision-3", "", "", "2013-01-30 13:22:16", "2013-01-30 13:22:16", "", "2065", "http://escpd.com/2065-revision-3/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
