/h2>\nYeti have been around for many, many years. It was a Yeti C-26 which John Tomac put some drop bars on for the 1990 World Champs in Durango.\nWell, they\'ve come a long, long way since then and the 575 shows they\'ve learnt a thing or two about putting gorgeous looking bikes together.\nShort, light and flickable but burly and robust - great for whatever you chuck yourself at.\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Yeti 575\" href=\"http://www.yeticycles.com/#/bikes/575\">Learn more about the Yeti 575</a>\n\n[image] http://www.yeticycles.com/#/bikes/575\n<h2>Santa Cruz Nomad Carbon</h2>\nI\'ve posted this bike in full <a title=\"Santa Cruz Carbon Nomad\" href=\"http://escpd.com/santa-cruz-carbon-nomad/\">on here previously</a>, so I won\'t risk repeating myself.\nIt\'s an awesome bike and one which would sit in my shed asking me when we\'re next going out.\nAwesome in white, most awesome in matte black.\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Santa Cruz Nomad Carbon \" href=\"http://www.santacruzbicycles.com/nomad_carbon/\">Learn more about the Santa Cruz Nomad Carbon</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPrices from £4,000\n\n[image]http://brimages.bikeboardmedia.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/04/santa-cruz-carbon-fiber-nomad2.jpg\n<h2>Devinci Dixon Carbon RX Evo</h2>\nNo country has better facilities for gnarly mountain biking than Canada - and that\'s where Devinci rip up the trails with their uber-steeds.\nHere\'s what they say about the Dixon: \"This hammer strong bike is pure stoke.\"\nI\'ve ridden one and I\'m like totally dialled into that, braa.\nLeonardo would say the same.\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Devinci Dixon Carbon RX Evo\" href=\"http://www.devinci.com/bikes/bike_326_scategory_83\">Learn more about the Devinci Dixon Carbon RX Evo</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\nPrice: £3,599\n\n<a title=\"Freeborn Bikes\" href=\"http://www.freeborn.co.uk/devinci-dixon-carbon-rx-bike-2013\">Buy online from Freeborn Bicycles</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[image]http://assets1.freeborn.co.uk/media/catalog/product/cache/1/image/5e06319eda06f020e43594a9c230972d/2/0/2013---dixon_carbon_rx.jpg\n<h2>Commencal Meta AM 1</h2>\nIt\'s a pretty sure bet that if you live and work in the Alps and design bikes which rule in the high mountains.\nAndorra based Commencal do just that and the Meta AM1 has a compact cockpit and a low bottom bracket so that cornering at speed is effortless. Although not one of the lightest bikes out there it\'s one of the most capable trail sleds you can get.\n\nPrice: £3,999.99\n\n<a title=\"Buy online from ChainReactioncycles\" href=\"http://www.chainreactioncycles.com/Models.aspx?ModelID=83508&amp;gclid=CKXHm7eTkLUCFebLtAodxTgApg\">Buy online from ChainReactioncycles</a>\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Commencal Meta AM1\" href=\"http://www.commencal-store.co.uk/PBSCProduct.asp?ItmID=10252609\">Learn more about the Commencal Meta AM1</a>\n\n&lt;iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/53141820\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;\n\n[image]http://www.commencal.com/web_bicycles/2013/HD_2013/bikes_2013/all_mountain/META_AM1_013.jpg\n<h2>Transition Covert Carbon</h2>\nI\'ve had this nagging feeling that I\'ve been missing something in my life since I first saw a picture of the Covert.\nSince then, <a title=\"Transition Covert\" href=\"http://escpd.com/transition-covert/\">I\'ve written an article about it</a>, done a budget to see if I could ever afford to buy one, considered selling a body part or a family member and dreamt of shredding my trails with this bike.\nI\'ll never be as good a rider as Andrea Bruno, but somehow that seems irrelevant.\n&lt;iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/52691278\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitAllowFullScreen mozallowfullscreen allowFullScreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;\n\nPrices from: £2,400 (frame only)\n\n<a title=\"Learn more about the Transition Covert Carbon\" href=\"http://www.transitionbikes.com/2013/Bikes_Covert26Carbon_1.cfm\">Learn more about the Transition Covert Carbon</a>\n\n[image]http://gp1.pinkbike.org/p4pb8341143/p4pb8341143.jpg", "Favor8 All Mountain Bikes", "", "inherit", "closed", "open", "", "2065-revision-4", "", "", "2013-01-30 13:50:10", "2013-01-30 13:50:10", "", "2065", "http://escpd.com/2065-revision-4/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
